{"text": "xHBdG=\u0000[\u001cxHBdG]T: (44)\n\nThus, the matrix A=\u001cxHBdGassociated with the BdG Hamiltonian HBdGis anti-symmetric\n\nand can be used to compute the Pfa\u000ean. Similar to the Pfa\u000ean of the projected Hamiltonian\n\nEq. 42, the Pfa\u000ean of the full Hamiltonian Pf[HBdG\u001cx] changes sign at a zero-energy level\n\ncrossing. This suggests that the sgn[ Pf[HBdG\u001cx]] as a topological invariant.\n\nFor translationally invariant systems, the BdG Hamiltonian is characterized by crystal\n\nmomentum k. Out of these only HBdG(k) is particle-hole symmetric only at k= 0;\u0019, which\n\nare the only values of kthat satisfy k\u0011\u0000kmodulo 2\u0019. While we might be tempted to use\n\nsgn[Pf[HBdG(k= 0;\u0019)\u001cx]] as a two component Z2topological invariant, one can see that\n\na disconnected chain of systems with sgn[ Pf[HBdG\u001cx]] =\u00061, which would be trivial. Such\n\ntrivial systems would be characterized by sgn[ Pf[HBdG(k= 0;\u0019)\u001cx]] = sgn[Pf[HBdG\u001cx]].\n\n20\n\nThis suggests the topological invariant for superconductors constructed by Kitaev29,\n\nQ= sgn [Pf[\u001cxHK(k= 0)]Pf[\u001cxHK(k=\u0019)]]: (45)\n\nThis topological invariant also provides information about the two dimensional topological\n\nsuperconductors, which are usually described by a Chern number topological invariant.\n\nSpeci\n\ncally, the topological invariant Eq. 45 determines the parity of the Chern number in\n\ntwo dimensional topological superconductors, which is exactly the condition for obtaining\n\nodd number of Majorana modes in vortex cores41.\n\nThe change in the sign of the Pfa\u000ean between k= 0 andk=\u0019i.e. the topological\n\ninvariant Eq. 45 can be associated with the existence of end Majorana modes for open\n\nboundary conditions, thus proving a bulk-boundary correspondence. To see this, let us\n\nstart by considering a long ring of the system with periodic boundary conditions with an\n\nodd number of unit cells L. The allowed momentum in that case is k= 2\u0019n=L , includes\n\nk= 0 and a set of ( k;\u0000k) pairs for n < (L+ 1)=2.", "embedding": [-0.012115143, 0.015590561, 0.008735921, 0.02158883, 0.026466893, -0.009740611, 0.007887392, -0.019079326, -0.06543037, 0.07892298, 0.010000646, 0.00082014344, 0.03147146, -0.05600271, -0.0036971276, 0.04168008, -0.018692533, -0.041647736, -0.0803955, 0.0047640805, 0.0414683, 0.008125149, -0.05283741, -0.015217519, 0.01820187, 0.061988804, 0.027112642, 0.039547864, 0.04462661, 0.023257613, 0.038052015, -0.013337118, 0.00066881854, -0.032330178, -0.0033885988, 0.028458914, -0.020619255, -0.028312089, 0.044358835, -0.0117398305, 0.054674696, -0.03570037, 0.009247752, -0.02644554, -0.0077044964, 0.006931141, -0.024554249, 0.0098692365, -0.015555383, -0.08331936, -0.0073539717, -0.0043514147, 0.038291432, -0.017091518, -0.0033800357, 0.017769765, -0.014828718, 0.0017386691, -0.01002811, -0.0013921586, 0.017867308, -0.026182147, 0.009441246, -0.064546034, 0.04590743, 0.01710857, 0.03624269, 0.046218973, -0.03129996, -0.05944812, -0.015098208, 0.0066766, -0.013868192, -0.030563792, -0.047744274, 0.024524508, 0.034308385, -0.0597044, -0.077616945, -0.040064614, -0.020217167, -0.009701654, -0.022298267, -0.0077684103, -0.010153812, -0.026448818, -0.00094383286, -0.017905243, 0.00026057218, -0.0012123773, 0.04364603, 0.045180716, -0.02116854, 0.01592565, 0.028223755, 0.018812966, -0.027295094, 0.037448242, 0.017391369, 0.0062999567, 0.005049127, 0.040748235, -0.041201603, 0.071183644, -0.047887567, 0.0061970986, 0.013845444, 0.026213031, -0.004998338, -0.049475685, 0.04740726, 0.0029725612, 0.015156463, 0.022175003, 0.01463653, 0.012906289, 0.035039406, 0.021883287, -0.033223856, -0.018528106, 0.008767916, -0.030153567, 0.061328422, 0.02742425, -0.03175228, 0.001005002, 0.034173783, 0.025902385, -0.039356172, 0.012703085, 0.038943794, 0.017985245, -0.029606469, 0.01491954, -0.040139478, 0.008478647, -0.048090372, 0.025185963, 0.03400875, 0.009586132, 0.050